00:16:34,930 --> 00:16:36,260
不过他乱放字条
but he got mixed up.

193
00:16:36,730 --> 00:16:39,250
我的方法更有效
I have a more graceful solution to the memory problem.

194
00:16:42,770 --> 00:16:44,460
我有条不紊
I'm disciplined and organized.

195
00:16:45,400 --> 00:16:47,900
所以能够应付日常生活
I use habit and routine to make my life possible.

196
00:16:48,940 --> 00:16:51,000
萨米没有推动力去帮自己记忆
Sammy had no drive, no reason to make it work.

197
00:16:53,110 --> 00:16:53,840
我呢？
Me?

198
00:16:54,210 --> 00:16:55,700
“约翰・G奸杀我妻子”

199
00:16:56,080 --> 00:16:57,280
我有推动力
I got a reason.

200
00:17:15,330 --> 00:17:18,700
今午一点见娜塔莉娅取消息
"Today, 1:00 p.m. Meet Natalie for info.

201
00:17:19,540 --> 00:17:22,840
她也失去爱人，会同情你、帮你
"She has also lost someone. She will help you out of pity."

202
00:17:40,760 --> 00:17:42,420
-你是娜塔莉娅？
-你记不得我
-Natalie?
-You don't remember me.

203
00:17:43,260 --> 00:17:45,250
对不起，我应该解释，我有…
I'm sorry. I should have explained. I have this...

204
00:17:45,500 --> 00:17:46,560
你解释过，莱尼
You did explain, Lenny.

205
00:17:47,220 --> 00:17:49,560
请叫我莱纳，我太太叫我莱尼
Please call me Leonard. My wife called me Lenny.

206
00:17:49,870 --> 00:17:51,060
我知道，你说过
Yeah, I know. You told me.

207
00:17:51,340 --> 00:17:53,170
可能也说过讨厌叫莱尼
Then I probably told you how much I hated it.

208
00:17:55,840 --> 00:17:58,770
可以取下墨镜吗？
Do you mind taking your glasses off? It's hard for me to...

209
00:18:00,350 --> 00:18:01,140
谢谢
Thanks.

210
00:18:02,050 --> 00:18:03,350
你有消息给我？
So you have information for me?

211
00:18:03,620 --> 00:18:05,070
你的字条那样写？
Is that what your little note says?

212
00:18:06,380 --> 00:18:09,340
单靠字条生活，一定很辛苦
Must be tough living your life according to a couple of scraps of paper.

213
00:18:09,790 --> 00:18:11,240
洗衣单和杂货单调乱
Mix your laundry list with your grocery list,

214
00:18:11,490 --> 00:18:13,480
那就麻烦了
and you'll end up eating your underwear.

215
00:18:14,290 --> 00:18:16,960
所以你甚至备忘纹在身上
I guess that's why you have those freaky tattoos.

216
00:18:18,060 --> 00:18:20,690
日子确实不好过
Yeah, it's tough. It's almost impossible.

217
00:18:21,870 --> 00:18:24,630
记不得你，对不起，不要见怪
Look, I'm sorry I don't remember you. It's nothing personal.

218
00:18:27,440 --> 00:18:29,360
我的确有消息给你
I do have information for you.

219
00:18:30,440 --> 00:18:32,210
你给我个车牌
You gave me a license plate number.

220
00:18:33,480 --> 00:18:35,570
我去交通部查过
Had my friend at D.M.V. Trace it.

221
00:18:36,550 --> 00:18:38,380
猜猜是谁的
Guess what name came up.

222
00:18:39,820 --> 00:18:42,450
约翰・爱德华・盖玛，约翰・G
John Edward Gammell. John G.

223
00:18:43,160 --> 00:18:43,950
你认识他？
Do you know him?

224
00:18:44,320 --> 00:18:48,050
不过照片上的人看起来很熟悉
No, But his face on his driver's license looked really familiar.

225
00:18:48,360 --> 00:18:50,590
他可能来过酒吧
I think he's been in the bar, maybe.

226
00:18:50,960 --> 00:18:54,020
这是他车牌、照片副本
Here's a copy of his license, his registration, photo and all.

227
00:18:54,970 --> 00:18:56,420
你真的要这样做？
Are you sure you want this?

228
00:18:56,840 --> 00:18:58,960
-我有没有说过他做过什么？
-有
-Have I told you what this man did?
-Yeah.

229
00:18:59,440 --> 00:19:00,840
那你就不用问了
Then you shouldn't have to ask.

230
00:19:01,140 --> 00:19:03,670
不过，你即使报了仇…
But even if you get revenge, you're not gonna remember it.

231
00:19:04,180 --> 00:19:06,040
你也不会记得
You're not even gonna know that it happened.

232
00:19:06,350 --> 00:19:07,740
妻子的仇不可不报
My wife deserves vengeance.

233
00:19:08,010 --> 00:19:09,670
记不记得无所谓
Doesn't make any difference whether I know about it.

234
00:19:09,950 --> 00:19:11,540
即使记不得
Just because there are things I don't remember

235
00:19:11,850 --> 00:19:13,650
依然值得做
doesn't make my actions meaningless.

236
00:19:13,990 --> 00:19:16,720
即使闭上眼睛，世界并没有消失
The world doesn't just disappear when you close your eyes, does it?

237
00:19:17,920 --> 00:19:21,280
我可以拍张照片来提醒自已
Anyway, maybe I'll take a photograph to remind myself,

238
00:19:21,860 --> 00:19:23,620
或者再纹个备忘录在身上
get another freaky tattoo.

239
00:19:28,370 --> 00:19:29,630
再说说她的事吧
Tell me about her again.

240
00:19:31,870 --> 00:19:32,700
为什么？
Why?

241
00:19:33,010 --> 00:19:34,600
因为你喜欢记起她
Because you like to remember her.

242
00:19:37,440 --> 00:19:38,710
她漂亮
She was beautiful.

243
00:19:41,250 --> 00:19:42,940
对我来说，她是完美的
-To me, she was perfect.
-No.

244
00:19:43,380 --> 00:19:45,940
不要顺口说
Don't just recite the words.

245
00:19:47,250 --> 00:19:50,920
闭上眼睛去回忆她
Close your eyes... and remember her.

246
00:20:02,270 --> 00:20:04,100
我可以感受到细节
You can just feel the details.

247
00:20:06,670 --> 00:20:09,230
一些平时懒得回忆的细节
The bits and pieces you never bothered to put into words.

248
00:20:14,150 --> 00:20:16,440
那些非常时刻…
And you can feel these extreme moments...

249
00:20:17,480 --> 00:20:18,880
重现眼前
even if you don't want to.

250
00:20:21,990 --> 00:20:24,580
印像愈发清晰
You put these together, and you get the feel of a person.

251
00:20:28,090 --> 00:20:30,190
我更怀念她
Enough to know how much you miss them...

252
00:20:35,930 --> 00:20:38,630
也更痛恨凶手
and how much you hate the person who took them away.

253
00:20:48,510 --> 00:20:51,780
我…我写了个地址在上面
I, um... I added an address in here.

254
00:20:52,080 --> 00:20:55,320
也许有用，是近郊的一间荒屋
It might be useful. It's an abandoned place outside of town.

255
00:20:55,690 --> 00:20:58,780
我的朋友曾经在那里贩毒
A guy I knew used to do bigger deals there.

256
00:21:01,130 --> 00:21:02,490
四周没有人
It's isolated.

257
00:21:02,830 --> 00:21:04,020
好极了
Sounds perfect.

258
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:08,260
我应不应该付你…
Do I owe you any...

259
00:21:08,600 --> 00:21:10,090
不用，我不是为钱
I wasn't helping you for money.

260
00:21:10,640 --> 00:21:11,500
对不起
I'm sorry.

261
00:21:11,840 --> 00:21:14,670
不要紧，我知道你有病
It's okay. See, you have this condition.

262
00:21:16,980 --> 00:21:20,930
还住在优惠旅馆？你遗留在我家
Oh, are you still staying at the Discount Inn, room 304? You left it at my place.

263
00:21:29,860 --> 00:21:32,240
-旅馆招待好吗？
-我记不得
-They treating you okay?
-I don't remember.

264
00:21:35,990 --> 00:21:37,430
你和我有个共同点
You know what we have in common?

265
00:21:39,060 --> 00:21:41,450
我们都懂得生存
We are both survivors.

266
00:21:44,770 --> 00:21:46,140
保重，莱纳
You take care, Leonard.

267
00:22:14,870 --> 00:22:16,730
记住杰克斯・萨米
"Remember Sammy Jankis."

268
00:22:18,300 --> 00:22:21,760
我本来在保险公司服务
I met Sammy through work. Insurance. I was an investigator.

269
00:22:22,110 --> 00:22:24,670
负责调查保险索偿
I'd investigate the claims to see which ones were phony.

270
00:22:25,040 --> 00:22:26,480
专长是辨别真与假
I had to see through people's bullshit.

271
00:22:27,110 --> 00:22:29,240
这专长现在派上大用场
It was useful experience, 'cause now it's my life.

272
00:22:30,150 --> 00:22:32,340
现在我靠观察去辨认…
When I meet someone, I don't know if I've met them before.

273
00:22:33,550 --> 00:22:35,850
眼前的人是不是相识的
I have to look in their eyes and try and figure them out.

274
00:22:36,150 --> 00:22:37,680
我知道
My job taught me the best way to find out...

275
00:22:38,060 --> 00:22:39,220
观言辨色…
what someone knew was just to let them talk...

276
00:22:39,560 --> 00:22:41,550
是了解人的最好办法
and watch the eyes and the body language.

277
00:22:41,860 --> 00:22:43,730
譬如，一边谈话一边擦鼻子…
If someone scratches their nose while they're talking,

278
00:22:44,060 --> 00:22:46,900
那个人可能在说谎或者紧张
experts tell you it means they're lying. It really means they're nervous.

279
00:22:47,200 --> 00:22:50,330
紧张的原因很多，视乎情形而定
People get nervous for all sorts of reasons. It's all about context.

280
00:22:50,700 --> 00:22:51,790
对，我是观人高手
Yeah, I was good.

281
00:22:52,270 --> 00:22:55,070
第一个观察的人是萨米
Sammy was my first real challenge.

282
00:23:01,310 --> 00:23:02,110
莱尼！
Yo, Lenny!

283
00:23:03,180 --> 00:23:04,340
还以为你离开了本地
I thought you split for good.

284
00:23:04,650 --> 00:23:07,450
-情况有变
-看得出来
-Well, things change.
-So I see.

285
00:23:07,790 --> 00:23:08,650
我叫泰迪
My name's Teddy.

286
00:23:09,090 --> 00:23:10,820
我大概提到过我的病
I guess I've told you about my condition.

287
00:23:11,090 --> 00:23:12,420
每次见面都提
Only every time I see you.

288
00:23:13,260 --> 00:23:14,350
来，我请你吃午餐
Come on, I'll buy you lunch.

289
00:23:20,600 --> 00:23:22,690
-我有没有提过杰克斯・萨米？
-有
-Have I told you about Sammy Jankis?
-Mm. Yeah.

290
00:23:23,140 --> 00:23:24,530
我听得好厌
I'm sick of hearing about the guy.

291
00:23:25,290 --> 00:23:27,330
约翰・G呢？你认为他还在？
What about John G? you think he still here?

292
00:23:27,520 --> 00:23:29,740
-谁？
-约翰・G，你要找的人
-Who?
-Johnny G., the guy you're looking for.

293
00:23:30,110 --> 00:23:31,740
你为了找他，才留在本地？
That's why you haven't left town, am I right?

294
00:23:32,110 --> 00:23:32,600
也许吧
Maybe.

295
00:23:32,910 --> 00:23:35,110
莱纳，你非小心不可
Leonard, look, you have to be very careful.

296
00:23:35,610 --> 00:23:35,940
为什么？
Why?

297
00:23:36,080 --> 00:23:39,080
你提过有人想误导你…
The other day you mentioned that maybe somebody was trying to set you up,

298
00:23:39,790 --> 00:23:40,980
让你杀错人
get you to kill the wrong guy.

299
00:23:41,250 --> 00:23:43,740
我会凭事实去判断
Well, I go on facts, not recommendations, but thank you.

300
00:23:44,360 --> 00:23:47,480
怎能凭字条、照片去决定杀谁？
Lenny, you can't trust a man's life to your little notes and pictures.

301
00:23:47,790 --> 00:23:50,390
-为什么不能？
-因为字条未必可靠
-Why not?
-Because your notes could be unreliable.

302
00:23:50,630 --> 00:23:51,890
-记忆也未必可靠
-谢谢你的好心
-Memory's unreliable.
-Oh, please!

303
00:23:52,160 --> 00:23:54,330
记忆不准确，甚至不合用
No, really. Memory's not perfect. It's not even that good.

304
00:23:54,770 --> 00:23:55,630
问问警察吧
Ask the police.

305
00:23:56,130 --> 00:23:57,530
目击证供未必可靠
Eyewitness testimony is unreliable.

306
00:23:58,140 --> 00:24:00,430
警察不是凭记忆缉凶
Cops don't catch a killer by remembering stuff.

307
00:24:00,810 --> 00:24:01,240
我明白
Right...

308
00:24:01,640 --> 00:24:04,470
-警察搜集事实，做笔记，然后作出结沦
-那不是我的意思
They collect facts, they make notes, and they draw conclusions.

309
00:24:04,510 --> 00:24:06,000
凭事实，不是凭记忙
Facts, not memories.

310
00:24:06,240 --> 00:24:08,840
我以前是调查员，所以知道
That's how you investigate. It's what I used to do.

311
00:24:09,180 --> 00:24:12,450
形状、颜色等细节，未必记得准
Look, memory can change the shape of a room. It can change the color of a car.

312
00:24:13,020 --> 00:24:14,650
可以记错
And memories can be distorted.

313
00:24:15,220 --> 00:24:17,350
记忆只是一种演译，不是纪录
They're just an interpretation. They're not a record.

314
00:24:17,660 --> 00:24:19,390
掌握事实，就不用靠记忆
They're irrelevant if you have the facts.

315
00:24:20,360 --> 00:24:22,120
你非报仇不可？
You really want to get this guy, don't you?

316
00:24:22,660 --> 00:24:25,150
他杀死我的妻子，夺去我的记忆
He killed my wife. He took away my fucking memory.

317
00:24:28,300 --> 00:24:30,000
毁灭我生存的能力
He destroyed my ability to live.

318
00:24:34,210 --> 00:24:34,900
你还活着
You're living.

319
00:24:36,810 --> 00:24:38,140
完全为了报仇
Only for revenge.

320
00:24:38,840 --> 00:24:40,140
那么我们把这坏蛋找出来
Well, then we'll get the bastard.

321
00:24:40,550 --> 00:24:41,440
你住在哪里？
Where are you staying?

322
00:24:44,680 --> 00:24:45,640
特惠旅馆
The Discount Inn.

323
00:24:48,050 --> 00:24:49,610
我不知道是哪间房间，我没有钥匙
I don't know what room. I haven't got my key.

324
00:24:49,890 --> 00:24:50,880
可能留在房里
Probably left in in your room.

325
00:25:07,340 --> 00:25:09,500
我是房客，不见了钥匙
I'm checked in here, but I think I've misplaced my key.

326
00:25:10,010 --> 00:25:11,030
你好，莱纳
How you doing, Leonard?

327
00:25:11,840 --> 00:25:13,240
可能在房里
Probably in the room, right?

328
00:25:32,400 --> 00:25:34,960
-我的钥匙呢？
-糟糕，进错房间了
-I don't see my key anywhere.
-This is the wrong room.

329
00:25:35,270 --> 00:25:37,330
-你现在住304号
-对不起，我搞错了
-You're in 304 now.
-I'm sorry. I fucked up.

330
00:25:37,740 --> 00:25:39,030
-这不是我的房间？
-不是你的房间
-This is not my room?
-No.

331
00:25:39,040 --> 00:25:39,870
我们走吧
Come on, let's go.

332
00:25:40,970 --> 00:25:41,900
为什么有我的笔迹？
Why is this my handwriting?

333
00:25:42,010 --> 00:25:43,740
剃左腿

334
00:25:47,280 --> 00:25:49,940
以前是，现在你住304
This was your room, but now you're in 304.

335
00:25:50,250 --> 00:25:51,940
-我什么时候住过这间？
-上个星期
-When was I in here?
-Last week.

336
00:25:52,350 --> 00:25:54,550
不过我再多租你一间
But then I rented you another room on top of it.

337
00:25:54,850 --> 00:25:55,480
为什么？
Why?

338
00:25:55,790 --> 00:25:59,020
生意冷淡…你既然有这种病…
Business is slow. I mean, I told my boss about the...

339
00:25:59,320 --> 00:26:01,710
我们于是多租一间给你
your condition and stuff, and he said try and rent him another room.

340
00:26:02,060 --> 00:26:04,260
我究竟租了几间？
So how many rooms am I checked into in this shit-hole?

341
00:26:04,530 --> 00:26:06,490
只是两间，到目前为止
Just two, so far.

342
00:26:07,070 --> 00:26:10,420
起码你坦白承认占我便宜
Well, at least you're being honest about ripping me off.

343
00:26:10,770 --> 00:26:12,570
你反正不会记得
Well, you're not gonna remember anyway.

344
00:26:13,410 --> 00:26:14,670
用不着那样坦白
You don't have to be that honest, Burt.

345
00:26:15,270 --> 00:26:16,000
莱纳
Leonard,

346
00:26:16,640 --> 00:26:18,440
每次都应该取收条
always get a receipt.

347
00:26:19,310 --> 00:26:20,900
我会记下来
Oh, yeah. I'm gonna write that down.

348
00:26:21,380 --> 00:26:23,750
“今午一点见娜塔莉娅取消息”

349
00:26:24,080 --> 00:26:25,480
-现在几点了？
-12点45分
-Hey, what time is it?
-Quarter to one.

350
00:26:27,290 --> 00:26:28,950
对不起
Excuse me.

351
00:26:29,790 --> 00:26:30,690
你房间的…
Your room's...

352
00:26:43,540 --> 00:26:45,200
-娜塔莉娅
-你记不得我
-Natalie?
-You don't remember me.

353
00:26:46,300 --> 00:26:48,670
杰克斯・萨米的保险索赔…
I'd just become an investigator when I came across Sammy.

354
00:26:49,010 --> 00:26:52,430
十分奇特，是我接手的第一宗案子
Mr. Samuel R. Jankis. Strangest case ever.

355
00:26:52,810 --> 00:26:55,470
萨米58岁，半退休会计师
Now, the guy's a 58-year-old semiretired accountant.

356
00:26:55,710 --> 00:26:58,080
遇到交通意外，本来不算严重
He and his wife had been in this car accident. Nothing too serious.

357
00:26:58,380 --> 00:27:01,180
奇怪的是，他记不住东西
But he's acting funny. He can't get a handle on what's going on.

358
00:27:02,690 --> 00:27:05,710
医生怀疑脑部受伤
The doctors find some possible damage to the hippocampus.

359
00:27:05,760 --> 00:27:07,550
但无法证实
Nothing conclusive,

360
00:27:07,630 --> 00:27:10,120
萨米的记忆只有几分钟
but Sammy can't remember anything for more than a couple of minutes.

361
00:27:10,430 --> 00:27:11,690
于是什么都不能做
Can't work, can't do shit.

362
00:27:11,960 --> 00:27:14,520
医药费昂贵，他的妻子通知了保险公司
The medical bills pile up. His wife calls the insurance company,

363
00:27:14,830 --> 00:27:15,730
公司派我调查
and I get sent in.

364
00:27:16,470 --> 00:27:20,730
我初次查案，于是查得格外认真
Now, this is my first big claims investigation, so I really check into it.

365
00:27:21,340 --> 00:27:22,000
要不要咖啡？
Can I get you some coffee?

366
00:27:22,070 --> 00:27:23,530
萨米思考没问题
Sammy can think just fine,

367
00:27:23,980 --> 00:27:24,500
不用客气

368
00:27:24,640 --> 00:27:26,040
不过，他没有新记忆
